channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 9/11 alleged mastermind Khalid Sheikh Mohammed and 2 others reach plea deal
item.description: Three of the five 9/11 defendants at Guantanamo have reached a plea agreement with prosecutors, the Department of Defense announced Wednesday.

item.description: Patterns like those of birds and bees are influencing Dutch scientists' research on "self-flying" swarms of tiny drones.

Unlawful border crossings reach lowest level since September 2020
item.description: U.S. Border Patrol agents made fewer than 60,000 migrant apprehensions along the U.S.-Mexico border in July, the lowest number since September 2020.

item.title: Man 'intentionally' runs over flock of 25 seagulls with his jeep at the beach: Police
item.description: A man has “intentionally” run over and killed a flock of 25 seagulls with his Jeep Cherokee before almost running over two people and their dogs, authorities said.

item.description: Securing the Paris Olympics has involved a veritable army of police and military forces. They've had their hands full but, so far, mostly thwarting minor threats.
